723975f-a.text:
Washington Place, north side, west from Green Street to Washington Square East. The white marble structure at the latter point is the University of the City of New York (1832-5). In the 1890's this building will be removed and a new one erected here that will be partially used for commercial purposes. At the left margin is the park identifying this locale.
About 1892
